{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17609986","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17609986"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:54:13+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:54:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16135"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16135","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16135"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.41,0.21,0.21,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8826"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64036"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8826","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8826"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16135"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49467"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"8108"},{"type":"tags","id":"8542"},{"type":"tags","id":"9982"},{"type":"tags","id":"10623"},{"type":"tags","id":"10628"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21054"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21057"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64036","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64036"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 30-year-old woman is in her third trimester of pregnancy and is preparing for labour and delivery. She has no significant medical history and her pregnancy has been uncomplicated. She does not take any regular medications. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDuring the third trimester, a specific immune environment is required to facilitate labour and delivery.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following immune environments and responses is required during the third trimester for labour and delivery?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Anti-inflammatory; Th-1","Anti-inflammatory; Th-2","Pro-inflammatory; Th-1","Pro-inflammatory; Th-2","Pro-inflammatory: Th-3"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring the third trimester of pregnancy, a \u003Cstrong\u003Epro-inflammatory\u003C/strong\u003E environment is necessary to initiate labour and delivery. This is because the process of labour involves the activation of inflammatory pathways that lead to cervical ripening, membrane rupture, and uterine contractions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003ETh-1\u003C/strong\u003E type immune response is associated with a pro-inflammatory state. Th-1 cells produce cytokines such as interferon-gamma and tumour necrosis factor-alpha, which promote inflammation. This response is crucial for the onset of labour.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAn \u003Cstrong\u003Eanti-inflammatory\u003C/strong\u003E environment, associated with a \u003Cstrong\u003ETh-2\u003C/strong\u003E response, is more characteristic of the earlier stages of pregnancy, where it helps to maintain a state of immune tolerance to the fetus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETherefore, the correct combination for the third trimester is a pro-inflammatory environment with a Th-1 type response.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The third trimester of pregnancy requires a pro-inflammatory environment to facilitate labour and delivery.","A Th-1 type immune response is associated with a pro-inflammatory state, which is necessary for the initiation of labour."],"references":["Mor G, Cardenas I, Abrahams V, Guller S. Inflammation and pregnancy: the role of the immune system at the implantation site. Ann N Y Acad Sci. 2011 Mar;1221(1):80-7. doi: 10.1111/j.1749-6632.2010.05938.x. PMID: 21401634; PMCID: PMC3078586","Mor G, Cardenas I. The immune system in pregnancy: a unique complexity. Am J Reprod Immunol. 2010 Jun;63(6):425-33. doi: 10.1111/j.1600-0897.2010.00836.x. Epub 2010 Mar 29. PMID: 20367629; PMCID: PMC3025805","Abu-Raya B, Michalski C, Sadarangani M, Lavoie PM. Maternal Immunological Adaptation During Normal Pregnancy. Front Immunol. 2020 Oct 7;11:575197. doi: 10.3389/fimmu.2020.575197. PMID: 33133091; PMCID: PMC7579415","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49467"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16135"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49467","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/49467"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-22T21:21:38+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-22T21:22:40+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8826"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64036"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://